headline: Airbnb posts Q3 revenue beat, slight profit miss. Here's why.
summary: Airbnb (ABNB) revealed a mixed third quarter performance after Thursday's market close, posting third quarter revenue of $3.73 billion — just above estimates of $3.72 billion — and adjusted earnings of $2.13 per share — just barely below forecasts of $2.15. The home and experience booker's stock is rising in extended hours (at the time of this video's posting) as the company raised its fourth quarter guidance. Yahoo Finance special reporter Akiko Fujita breaks down the earnings print, detailing Airbnb's growth in gross bookings value and nights booked. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime here. This post was written by Luke Carberry Mogan.

headline: Airbnb (NASDAQ:ABNB) Posts Q3 Sales In Line With Estimates, Stock Soars
summary: Online accommodations platform Airbnb (NASDAQ:ABNB) met Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q3 CY2024, with sales up 9.9% year on year to $3.73 billion. On the other hand, next quarter’s revenue guidance of $2.40 billion was less impressive, coming in 1.2% below analysts’ estimates. Its GAAP profit of $2.13 per share was also in line with analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Airbnb revenue narrowly beats on strong growth in international markets
summary: The travel company, which has been investing heavily to bolster its presence globally, said the average growth rate of nights booked on an origin basis in expansion markets was double that of its core markets in the third quarter.  Nights and experiences booked increased 8% to 122.8 million from a year earlier, led by growth of 19% in Asia-Pacific and 15% in Latin America.  Analysts expected quarterly revenue to come in at $3.72 billion.
